Phase 15 — Risk Assessment and Mitigation
Goal: Identify every technical risk before the first line of code is written.

For every risk:

Risk: [Name] Probability: Low / Medium / High Impact: Low / Medium / High Category: Performance / Compatibility / Security / UX / Legal / Technical Debt Description: [What could go wrong and why] Mitigation: [Concrete action taken during architecture or development to prevent this] Contingency: [What to do if it happens anyway]

Standard Android risks to evaluate for every app:

Background process killed by OS Mitigation: WorkManager, foreground services, save state in onStop

Memory leaks (context in singletons) Mitigation: Application context only, lifecycle-aware components

Large file handling causing OOM Mitigation: Stream processing, BitmapFactory inSampleSize, WorkManager

Android version fragmentation Mitigation: Explicit minSdk, AndroidX compat libraries, conditional API checks

Permission permanently denied Mitigation: Settings deep-link, graceful feature degradation

Battery optimization killing background work Mitigation: WorkManager constraints, FCM for wake-ups

Storage limit — no space left Mitigation: Check available space before write, catch IOException

Thread synchronization (race conditions) Mitigation: Coroutine structured concurrency, Mutex for shared state

Deep link hijacking Mitigation: Verify deep link origins, validate all deep link parameters

Sensitive data in logs Mitigation: Timber release tree that strips logs, no PII in log messages

App size bloat Mitigation: R8 optimization, WebP images, on-demand delivery (DFM)

Slow startup time Mitigation: App startup library, lazy DI, baseline profiles

Play Store policy violations Mitigation: Review current policies for photo/video, location, accessibility

Validation Checkpoint
Every risk has both a mitigation (proactive) and a contingency (reactive)
No risk is marked High probability + High impact without a mitigation strategy
