Phase 17 — AI Implementation Contract
Goal: Leave zero room for the coding agent to make architectural decisions. Every standard in this section is mandatory, not a suggestion.

LANGUAGE AND SDK

Programming Language: Kotlin only. No Java files. No mixed-language modules. Minimum SDK: [API level] (Rationale: [X]% device coverage) Target SDK: [current stable] Compile SDK: [same as Target SDK] Kotlin Version: [current stable]

UI FRAMEWORK

UI Framework: Jetpack Compose (or XML + ViewBinding — choose one, not both) Design System: Material 3 (Material You) Theme: [App theme name] supporting Light and Dark No XML layouts mixed with Compose. No View interop unless explicitly approved.

ARCHITECTURE

Pattern: MVVM + Clean Architecture (or stated deviation) Layers: Presentation → Domain → Data (no layer skip) State: UiState sealed class per screen, exposed as StateFlow Events: UiEffect sealed class, exposed as Flow via Channel No business logic in Composables, Fragments, or Activities. No Android imports in domain layer. No direct DAO access from ViewModel — always through Repository.

DEPENDENCY INJECTION

Framework: Hilt No manual object creation for classes managed by Hilt. No singleton anti-patterns. Use @Singleton scope via Hilt only.

ASYNC AND CONCURRENCY

Framework: Kotlin Coroutines and Flow No RxJava. No AsyncTask. No raw Thread(). IO work: Dispatchers.IO CPU-intensive: Dispatchers.Default UI: Dispatchers.Main.immediate ViewModel scope: viewModelScope only (no GlobalScope) Error handling: try/catch inside coroutines, wrapped in Result No exceptions swallowed silently.

NAVIGATION

Framework: Navigation Component (Compose Nav or XML Nav — one only) Single NavHost in MainActivity. No direct Activity starts for in-app navigation. All destinations registered in AppNavGraph.kt. All args passed via type-safe arguments.

DATABASE

Framework: Room DAOs return Flow for queries, suspend fun for writes. No raw SQL strings outside @Query annotations. No fallbackToDestructiveMigration in release builds. Preferences: DataStore only. No SharedPreferences.

NETWORKING (if applicable)

Framework: Retrofit + OkHttp Serialization: kotlinx.serialization (or Moshi — one only, not Gson) All API calls return Result — no raw exceptions propagating to ViewModel. Logging interceptor in debug builds only.

NAMING CONVENTIONS

Classes: PascalCase Functions/variables: camelCase Constants: SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE Resources (XML): snake_case ViewModels: [Feature]ViewModel.kt UiState: [Feature]UiState.kt Use Cases: [Verb][Noun]UseCase.kt Repositories: [Domain]Repository.kt (interface) / [Domain]RepositoryImpl.kt Entities: [Name]Entity.kt DTOs: [Name]Dto.kt Domain Models: [Name].kt (no suffix)

ERROR HANDLING STANDARDS

All errors surface to UiState.Error — never crash the app on recoverable errors. Network errors show a retry button. DB errors log and show generic error message to user. Fatal errors (developer mistakes) use require() / check() / error() — not silent nulls. No !! (non-null assertion) except in test code with explicit comment.

LOGGING STANDARDS

Framework: Timber Debug builds: Timber.plant(Timber.DebugTree()) Release builds: Timber.plant(CrashReportingTree()) — no logs to logcat No Log.d, Log.e, Log.i, Log.w, or println in source code. No PII in any log message.

TESTING REQUIREMENTS

Unit Tests: All Use Cases. All ViewModels. All Mappers. Integration Tests: Repository implementations with in-memory Room database. UI Tests: Critical user flows (login, primary feature, fatal error state). Test framework: JUnit 5 (or JUnit 4), MockK, Turbine. Test naming: [methodUnderTest][scenario][expectedResult] Minimum coverage: 80% on domain and data layers.

AGENT BEHAVIORAL RULES

Do NOT modify files outside the current phase's scope. Do NOT change the architecture pattern without explicit instruction. Do NOT add a library not listed in Phase 12 without flagging it first. Do NOT skip error handling. Placeholder implementations are not acceptable. Do NOT use deprecated APIs without explicit justification. Do NOT create duplicate implementations of existing abstractions. Return COMPLETE files — no ... or "rest remains the same" placeholders. After each phase, list every file created or modified. If a conflict is found with the blueprint, STOP and report it — do not resolve silently. When a decision is truly ambiguous, ask ONE specific question before proceeding.

